 stone, shouldn't he?

977
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:33,519
 He was a good-looking man
 when he was young.

978
00:56:33,520 --> 00:56:36,399
 - Was he?
 - Mm.

979
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:39,400
 He's got a good heart.

980
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:43,239
 Life's not always kind, is it?

981
00:56:43,240 --> 00:56:46,240
 No, it isn't, Gerri.

982
00:56:52,040 --> 00:56:55,040
 (low chatter)

983
00:56:57,280 --> 00:57:00,280
 l don't mind the grey hair.

984
00:57:00,880 --> 00:57:03,880
 l think that can look quite distinguished
 on a man of his age, but...

985
00:57:06,920 --> 00:57:09,920
 You know.

986
00:57:21,880 --> 00:57:24,880
 - l'll give you a ring in the week.
 - We'll have a proper game next time.

987
00:57:25,080 --> 00:57:28,080
 - Ta-ta.
 - See you.

988
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:35,079
 Hi, Joe.

989
00:57:35,080 --> 00:57:36,359
 Hi.

990
00:57:36,360 --> 00:57:38,319
 - Have you come back to me?
 - l have.

991
00:57:38,320 --> 00:57:40,599
 - They all come back in the end.
 - Do they?

992
00:57:40,600 --> 00:57:43,359
 - ln my nightmares.
 - Oh, it's as bad as that, is it?

993
00:57:43,360 --> 00:57:45,479
 Oh, let's not open that can ofworms.

994
00:57:45,480 --> 00:57:48,480
 - No, let's leave that closed.
 - Not today, anyway.

995
00:57:50,120 --> 00:57:52,199
 Oh, how are you, Joe?

996
00:57:52,200 --> 00:57:55,200
 - ls life treating you kind?
 - Can't complain.

997
00:57:55,760 --> 00:57:57,759
 - Really?
 - Yes.

998
00:57:57,760 --> 00:58:00,679
 Nothing you want to share with me?

999
00:58:00,680 --> 00:58:02,159
 No, l don't think so.

1000
00:58:02,160 --> 00:58:04,879
 Because you know that you can talk to me.

1001
00:58:04,880 --> 00:58:07,599
 Any time you like.

1002
00:58:07,600 --> 00:58:09,479
 Well, l'll come and find you if l need you.

1003
00:58:09,480 --> 00:58:11,639
 Yeah. Yeah.

1004
00:58:11,640 --> 00:58:14,640
 l like to feel that l'm always there for you.

1005
00:58:15,040 --> 00:58:16,599
 Thanks, Mary.

1006
00:58:16,600 --> 00:58:19,600
 How are you?

1007
00:58:21,000 --> 00:58:22,479
 Yeah, l'm all right.

1008
00:58:22,480 --> 00:58:24,039
 No, l'm great, actually.

1009
00:58:24,040 --> 00:58:25,999
 - Well, you look well.
 - Do l?

1010
00:58:26,000 --> 00:58:28,279
 Oh, thank you.

1011
00:58:28,280 --> 00:58:29,759
 l suddenly feel...

1012
00:58:29,760 --> 00:58:31,199
 really liberated.

1013
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:33,639
 - Well, you're a free spirit now.
 - l know.

1014
00:58:33,640 --> 00:58:36,640
 You're your own woman.
 The world's your oyster.

1015
00:58:37,000 --> 00:58:38,599
 lt's so exciting, isn't it?

1016
00:58:38,600 --> 00:58:41,600
 l feel like Thelma and Louise.

1017
00:58:41,760 --> 00:58:44,760
 This little car is going to change my life.

1018
00:58:44,800 --> 00:58:47,279
 Well, let's hope so.

1019
00:58:47,280 --> 00:58:50,280
 l do feel a bit guilty, though,
 but at the end ofthe day...

1020
00:58:51,000 --> 00:58:52,439
 ..so what?

1021
00:58:52,440 --> 00:58:54,199
 lt's my little present to me.

1022
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:56,679
 - That's fair enough.
 - Yeah.

1023
00:58:56,680 --> 00:58:59,680
 Because if l don't treat myself,
 nobody else is going to, are they?

1024
00:59:00,320 --> 00:59:03,079
 What are you going to call this car?

1025
00:59:03,080 --> 00:59:05,759
 Ooh, l don't know.
 Why? Do you give names to things?

1026
00:59:05,760 --> 00:59:08,079
 - l've got names for everything.
 - Really?

1027
00:59:08,080 --> 00:59:10,639
 - Like what?
 - Well, my nose is called Roger.

1028
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:12,399
 - Oh, you mean...
 - (giggles)

1029
00:59:12,400 --> 00:59:13,959
 ..your body parts!

1030
00:59:13,960 --> 00:59:16,960
 Yeah, l'm not going to introduce you
 to everyone though.

1031
00:59:18,280 --> 00:59:20,439
 What, not even little Percy?

1032
00:59:20,440 --> 00:59:23,440
 You've already met my knee, then?

1033
00:59:23,840 --> 00:59:26,199
 Oh, Joe, we must go out
 and have a drink one night.

1034
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:28,159
 - We have such a laugh.
 - Yeah, we do.

1035
00:59:28,160 --> 00:59:31,160
 You see, the thing about you and me is
 that we've always just sort of clicked.

1036
00:59:31,760 --> 00:59:33,399
 - Haven't we?
 - Yeah.

1037
00:59:33,400 --> 00:59:36,400
 Yeah.

1038
00:59:37,040 --> 00:59:40,040
 lt's nice when that happens, isn't it?

1039
00:59:44,440 --> 00:59:46,759
 Do you remember
 when you showed me your little box?

1040
00:59:46,760 --> 00:59:48,519
 Yes.

1041
00:59:48,520 --> 00:59:50,279
 You wouldn't tell me what was in it.

1042
00:59:50,280 --> 00:59:51,879
 l'm still not going to tell you.

1043
00:59:51,880 --> 00:59:53,079
 l know.

1044
00:59:53,080 --> 00:59:55,439
 What?

1045
00:59:55,440 --> 00:59:58,399
 l'm not telling you.

1046
00:59:58,400 --> 00:59:59,999
 l still think about that.

1047
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:03,000
 We had a barbeque that day, didn't we?

1048
01:00:03,080 --> 01:00:04,999
 Oh! lt still smells the same.

1049
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:07,599
 lt's messy, isn't it?

1050
01:00:07,600 --> 01:00:10,600
 Your kids will enjoy playing in here, won't they?

1051
01:00:11,640 --> 01:00:14,640
 One day.

1052
01:00:16,240 --> 01:00:19,199
 So, is there anyone special in your life
 at the moment, Joe?

1053
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:21,439
 - No.
 - Oh, good.

1054
01:00:21,440 --> 01:00:24,440
 No, what l mean is, that's all right.
 You're comfortable with that.

1055
01:00:24,480 --> 01:00:25,799
 - Aren't you?
 - Am l?

1056
01:00:25,800 --> 01:00:28,800
 Well, the thing is, Joe, you're young.
 You still want to be out there, don't you?

1057
01:00:29,400 --> 01:00:30,839
 What, sowing my wild oats?

1058
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:32,199
 Well, yeah.

1059
01:00:32,200 --> 01:00:35,200
 Live life while you can.
 Don't think about tomorrow.

1060
01:00:35,440 --> 01:00:37,839
 Well, a lot of my friends
 are getting married.

1061
01:00:37,840 --> 01:00:40,840
 Oh, but, yeah,
 you wanna be careful, Joe, because...

1062
01:00:42,920 --> 01:00:45,920
 See, l got married in my 20s
 and, granted he was the wrong man,

1063
01:00:47,240 --> 01:00:48,999
 but l was too young.

1064
01:00:49,000 --> 01:00:50,679
 l couldn't handle it.

1065
01:00:50,680 --> 01:00:53,680
 But when l was in my 30s,
 l met the right man and l was mature.

1066
01:00:55,080 --> 01:00:58,080
 l was ready for it.

1067
01:01:00,400 --> 01:01:03,400
 l mean, he left me, but...

1068
01:01:03,840 --> 01:01:06,840
 What can you do?

1069
01:01:08,080 --> 01:01:10,639
 lt's never too late, Mary.

1070
01:01:10,640 --> 01:01:12,599
 Oh, no, l know it isn't, Joe,

1071
01:01:12,600 --> 01:01:15,600
 and, you know me, l'm very much
 a glass-half-full kind of girl.

1072
01:01:17,000 --> 01:01:19,799
 But it's tricky, because...

1073
01:01:19,800 --> 01:01:22,800
 l meet these older men,
 who want somebody younger,

1074
01:01:22,920 --> 01:01:25,920
 and that's great, because l fit the bill.

1075
01:01:26,320 --> 01:01:27,559
 But...

1076
01:01:27,560 --> 01:01:30,560
 when they find out that...

1077
01:01:30,680 --> 01:01:33,319
 ..you know, l'm not as young
 as they thought...

1078
01:01:33,320 --> 01:01:36,320
 they don't want to know.

1079
01:01:36,880 --> 01:01:39,880
 My looks work against me.

1080
01:01:42,040 --> 01:01:45,040
 How old do you think l look, Joe?

1081
01:01:48,560 --> 01:01:50,719
 60?

1082
01:01:50,720 --> 01:01:51,919
 70?

1083
01:01:51,920 --> 01:01:54,920
 Oh, stop it.

1084
01:02:02,800 --> 01:02:05,319
 Oh, it's all right.
 You don't have to answer that.

1085
01:02:05,320 --> 01:02:07,479
 So, when are we going to have this drink?

1086
01:02:07,480 --> 01:02:09,639
 l don't know. l'll have to check my diary.

1087
01:02:09,640 --> 01:02:11,559
 - Yeah. You do that. Give me a call.
 - l will.

1088
01:02:11,560 --> 01:02:14,560
 - Promise.
 - l promise.

1089
01:02:21,320 --> 01:02:24,320
 Mate, got to get your train. We should get
 cracking. l'll run you to the station.

1090
01:02:25,160 --> 01:02:26,759
 You've had too much to drink, Tom.

1091
01:02:26,760 --> 01:02:28,439
 - No, l haven't.
 - l think you have.

1092
01:02:28,440 --> 01:02:30,519
 - l'm all right.
 - We can get him a mini cab.

1093
01:02:30,520 --> 01:02:33,479
 - No, l'll be fine on the tube.
 - You don't want to get a mini cab.

1094
01:02:33,480 --> 01:02:36,159
 lt might take 20 minutes to turn up.
 We haven't got time.

1095
01:02:36,160 --> 01:02:38,439
 l had a really bad experience
 in a mini cab once.

1096
01:02:38,440 --> 01:02:40,879
 - You're going on the tube, aren't you?
 - Of course.

1097
01:02:40,880 --> 01:02:43,880
 Don't go on the tube, Joe. l can give you a lift.
 You can be my navigator.

1098
01:02:44,040 --> 01:02:45,519
 - Ooh, that sounds fun.
 - Yeah.

1099
01:02:45,520 --> 01:02:48,039
 You can give them both a lift.
 All in the same direction.

1100
01:02:48,040 --> 01:02:51,040
 - l'm not sure Mary can manage that.
 - Of course l can. Oh, l don't know.

1101
01:02:51,160 --> 01:02:53,599
 - l'll be fine on the tube, honest.
 - lt's a great idea.

1102
01:02:53,600 --> 01:02:56,600
 - l don't know how to get to King's Cross.
 - l do. We can all go together.

1103
01:02:56,720 --> 01:02:59,639
 - Great. ls that all right with you, Mary?
 - Yeah, of course it is.

1104
01:02:59,640 --> 01:03:01,239
 lt'll be good practice for me.

1105
01:03:01,240 --> 01:03:03,679
 l'm going to run upstairs
 before we go on the journey.

1106
01:03:03,680 --> 01:03:05,279
 l'm not sure about this.

1107
01:03:05,280 --> 01:03:06,719
 lt'll be fine.

1108
01:03:06,720 --> 01:03:08,279
 Better pack my bag.

1109
01:03:08,280 --> 01:03:11,280
 - Tom.
 - What?

1110
01:03:11,880 --> 01:03:13,439
 What do you think, Tom?

1111
01:03:13,440 --> 01:03:15,759
 Well, it's small and red.
 lt's what you asked for.

1112
01:03:15,760 --> 01:03:18,279
 JOE: What have you done, Mary?
 - lt's great, isn't it?

1113
01:03:18,280 --> 01:03:21,239
 - Nice bit of parking, Mary.
 - Oh.

1114
01:03:21,240 --> 01:03:22,799
 Oh, God, l didn't lock it.

1115
01:03:22,800 --> 01:03:25,800
 lt's a good job it didn't get pinched, isn't it?

1116
01:03:27,080 --> 01:03:28,879
 By the way, Mary, it's a 1 .4.

1117
01:03:28,880 --> 01:03:30,879
 Oh.

1118
01:03:30,880 --> 01:03:33,880
 You must come again.
 Now you don't know the way.

1119
01:03:38,240 --> 01:03:41,240
 Oi, where are you going?

1120
01:03:53,480 --> 01:03:55,119
 Oh, God, Joe.

1121
01:03:55,120 --> 01:03:57,479
 - What am l going to do without you?
 - You'll be fine.

1122
01:03:57,480 --> 01:03:59,679
 Can't you stay just till we get to King's Cross?

1123
01:03:59,680 --> 01:04:02,680
 - We'll be all right, Mary.
 - Ken! You don't even know London.

1124
01:04:03,160 --> 01:04:04,639
 lt'll be signposted.

1125
01:04:04,640 --> 01:04:07,640
 lt's so lovely having you next to me, Joe,
 telling me where to go and what to do.

1126
01:04:08,160 --> 01:04:09,639
 lt's been a pleasure, Mary.

1127
01:04:09,640 --> 01:04:12,559
 Oh, please, l'll take you anywhere you want.
 l'll take you home.

1128
01:04:12,560 --> 01:04:14,039
 Just here will do.

1129
01:04:14,040 --> 01:04:17,040
 Oh, God. All right. Let me pull in.

1130
01:04:22,960 --> 01:04:25,079
 Oh, bye, then. But lovely to see you.

1131
01:04:25,080 --> 01:04:27,159
 - Don't forget to give me a ring.
 - No, l won't.

1132
01:04:27,160 --> 01:04:28,519
 - Bye, Joe.
 - Yeah, take care.

1133
01:04:28,520 --> 01:04:30,319
 - See you soon.
 - Look after yourself.

1134
01:04:30,320 --> 01:04:32,239
 - Oh, Joe, where do l go?
 - Straight ahead.

1135
01:04:32,240 --> 01:04:34,279
 - Left round the one-way system.
 - Yeah. OK.

1136
01:04:34,280 --> 01:04:35,839
 - Bye, then. Bye.
 - Yeah.

1137
01:04:35,840 --> 01:04:37,719
 - l'll get in the front now.
 - Oh, no, Ken.

1138
01:04:37,720 --> 01:04:40,319
 We haven't got time for this.

1139
01:04:40,320 --> 01:04:43,320
 Oh, for God's sake.

1140
01:04:44,440 --> 01:04:47,440
 Oh! No need to slam the door.

1141
01:04:56,840 --> 01:04:58,759
 - You better hurry up.
 - Yeah, l'll run.

1142
01:04:58,760 --> 01:05:00,479
 Yeah, l'll see you soon, then.

1143
01:05:00,480 --> 01:05:02,039
 - Goodbye, Mary.
 - Bye.

1144
01:05:02,040 --> 01:05:03,279
 Bye, Ken.

1145
01:05:03,280 --> 01:05:06,119
 - l like you, Mary. Can l phone you?
 - No, Ken. No.

1146
01:05:06,120 --> 01:05:09,120
 - l could come down and see you.
 - Take your hand off of me, please, Ken!

1147
01:05:09,320 --> 01:05:10,279
 Sorry.

1148
01:05:10,280 --> 01:05:12,039
 l'm going to have to be honest with you.

1149
01:05:12,040 --> 01:05:15,040
 l just don't have those kind offeelings
 for you, Ken. l'm really sorry.

1150
01:05:15,320 --> 01:05:18,320
 Right.

1151
01:05:19,240 --> 01:05:20,039
 Oh!

1152
01:05:20,040 --> 01:05:22,039
 Sorry, l got carried away.
 l didn't mean to.

1153
01:05:22,040 --> 01:05:24,599
 lt's all right. Hurry up.
 Your train is going in a minute.

1154
01:05:24,600 --> 01:05:27,600
 - Thanks for the lift.
 - Yeah, all right. Bye.

1155
01:05:28,440 --> 01:05:31,440
 God Almighty!

1156
01:06:46,920 --> 01:06:49,920
 - l'll put the kettle on.
 - The sooner the better.

1157
01:06:51,160 --> 01:06:52,519
 - Ohh!
 - Ohh!

1158
01:06:52,520 --> 01:06:54,919
 What are you doing here, you daft bugger?

1159
01:06:54,920 --> 01:06:56,479
 l've come to surprise you.

1160
01:06:56,480 --> 01:06:57,479
 Joe!

1161
01:06:57,480 --> 01:07:00,199
 - You certainly did that.
 - lt's lovely to see you.

1162
01:07:00,200 --> 01:07:01,159
 Ohh!

1163
01:07:01,160 --> 01:07:02,199
 Hello!

1164
01:07:02,200 --> 01:07:04,159
 Sorry. He made me hide behind the door.

1165
01:07:04,160 --> 01:07:06,799
 - You frightened the life out of me.
 - So, who's this, then?

1166
01:07:06,800 --> 01:07:08,479
 - Mum, Dad, this is Katie.
 - Hello.

1167
01:07:08,480 --> 01:07:11,480
 - This is Tom and Gerri.
 - Tom and Gerri? That's brilliant!

1168
01:07:11,680 --> 01:07:13,039
 Yeah, well...

1169
01:07:13,040 --> 01:07:15,279
 We've learnt to live with it over the years.

1170
01:07:15,280 --> 01:07:17,239
 - So, what's your name again?
 - Katie.

1171
01:07:17,240 --> 01:07:18,239
 Katie.

1172
01:07:18,240 --> 01:07:20,359
 - So have you been at the allotment?
 - Yes.

1173
01:07:20,360 --> 01:07:22,759
 Gathering the last ofthe season's harvest.

1174
01:07:22,760 --> 01:07:24,919
 We've brought back some lovely tomatoes.

1175
01:07:24,920 --> 01:07:27,679
 - Yeah.
 - Sounds gorgeous.

1176
01:07:27,680 --> 01:07:30,599
 - We were going to have a sandwich.
 - Are you both hungry?

1177
01:07:30,600 --> 01:07:32,359
 - l'm starving.
 - She's starving.

1178
01:07:32,360 --> 01:07:35,359
 - l'll just go and change.
 - Let me get out ofthis filthy clobber.

1179
01:07:35,360 --> 01:07:38,360
 - You go on through, Joe.
 - All right.

1180
01:07:39,960 --> 01:07:42,239
 KATlE:
 This is a lovely big kitchen, isn't it?

1181
01:07:42,240 --> 01:07:44,199
 - lt's gigantic.
 - Shut up!

1182
01:07:44,200 --> 01:07:47,039
 - Thank you for the flowers, Katie.
 - Glad you like them.

1183
01:07:47,040 --> 01:07:48,919
 - They're lovely.
 - They're all right.

1184
01:07:48,920 --> 01:07:50,879
 - Sit yourself down.
 - Thank you.

1185
01:07:50,880 --> 01:07:53,880
 - So how did you two meet?
 - Our eyes met across a crowded bar.

1186
01:07:54,120 --> 01:07:56,039
 We'd both been stood up by our dates.

1187
01:07:56,040 --> 01:07:58,959
 - Ah, the bonding ofthe jilted.
 - Something like that.

1188
01:07:58,960 --> 01:08:00,559
 - Pretty much.
 - When was this?

1189
01:08:00,560 --> 01:08:03,079
 - Oh, about three months ago, wasn't it?
 - Yeah.

1190
01:08:03,080 --> 01:08:05,359
 - You never told us.
 - Master of discretion.

1191
01:08:05,360 --> 01:08:07,919
 - l didn't know he had it in him.
 - My enigmatic son.

1192
01:08:07,920 --> 01:08:09,879
 - You know me.
 - Must be important.

1193
01:08:09,880 --> 01:08:12,880
 - Oh, he's a dark horse.
 - l wanted to keep you a secret.

1194
01:08:12,920 --> 01:08:15,920
 - You son's a weirdo!
 - Yes, we know. He's having treatment.

1195
01:08:16,240 --> 01:08:17,879
 Help yourself. Tuck in.

1196
01:08:17,880 --> 01:08:19,719
 - Whatever you want.
 - Thank you.

1197
01:08:19,720 --> 01:08:22,599
 - My mum and dad know all about you.
 - Do they now?

1198
01:08:22,600 --> 01:08:24,879
 - And what do they do, Katie?
 - Oh, my dad's a postman

1199
01:08:24,880 --> 01:08:26,599
 and my mum works
 on a make-up counter.

1200
01:08:26,600 --> 01:08:28,239
 - Oh, yeah?
 - What do you work at?

1201
01:08:28,240 --> 01:08:31,119
 - l'm an occupational therapist.
 - Oh, are you? Where do you work?

1202
01:08:31,120 --> 01:08:33,199
 - At the Royal Free.
 - That's a great hospital.

1203
01:08:33,200 --> 01:08:35,599
 - lt's pretty good.
 - Do you specialise?

1204
01:08:35,600 --> 01:08:38,039
 Yeah. Care ofthe elderly
 and stroke rehab.

1205
01:08:38,040 --> 01:08:39,999
 What's straight rehab?

1206
01:08:40,000 --> 01:08:41,479
 Stroke rehab.

1207
01:08:41,480 --> 01:08:43,039
 You are going deaf.

1208
01:08:43,040 --> 01:08:45,959
 Oh, stroke rehab.
 l thought you said straight rehab.

1209
01:08:45,960 --> 01:08:47,519
 What's straight rehab?

1210
01:08:47,520 --> 01:08:49,919
 What, for gay men who are on the turn?

1211
01:08:49,920 --> 01:08:52,920
