 on London's Victorian sewage system.

1234
01:09:53,560 --> 01:09:54,559
 Blimey.

1235
01:09:54,560 --> 01:09:56,519
 Eight metres? That's big.

1236
01:09:56,520 --> 01:09:59,520
 Oh, yeah. And it'll follow the path
 ofthe Thames for 20 miles,

1237
01:10:00,680 --> 01:10:02,479
 up to 80 metres underground.

1238
01:10:02,480 --> 01:10:04,799
 And that's just for this household.

1239
01:10:04,800 --> 01:10:06,639
 TOM:
 So, it's quite a big number.

1240
01:10:06,640 --> 01:10:09,239
 l'm not doing it on my own.
 There's a few of us.

1241
01:10:09,240 --> 01:10:11,919
 - lt won't be finished till after l'm dead.
 - Oh, no.

1242
01:10:11,920 --> 01:10:14,920
 You'd better get a move on.

1243
01:10:17,000 --> 01:10:19,039
 Help yourself.
 ls there anything you want?

1244
01:10:19,040 --> 01:10:21,439
 - Some ham?
 - Oh, no, thanks. l'm a veggie, actually.

1245
01:10:21,440 --> 01:10:22,719
 - Are you?
 - Mm.

1246
01:10:22,720 --> 01:10:24,799
 This cheese is gorgeous, though.
 Thank you.

1247
01:10:24,800 --> 01:10:26,559
 - Help yourself.
 - Thank you.

1248
01:10:26,560 --> 01:10:28,839
 - What have you got planned later?
 - Ah, yes.

1249
01:10:28,840 --> 01:10:31,279
 - We're having a visitation.
 - Sounds ominous.

1250
01:10:31,280 --> 01:10:33,639
 - Mary's coming for tea.
 - Oh, l was right.

1251
01:10:33,640 --> 01:10:35,999
 - Who's Mary?
 - She's a friend from work.

1252
01:10:36,000 --> 01:10:39,000
 - Oh, right.
 - Yes, she's... Yes.

1253
01:10:39,080 --> 01:10:40,879
 She's something else.

1254
01:10:40,880 --> 01:10:43,880
 l won't ask.

1255
01:10:46,080 --> 01:10:48,199
 - Ta-da!
 - Oh, Joe!

1256
01:10:48,200 --> 01:10:50,159
 How lovely to see you.

1257
01:10:50,160 --> 01:10:52,159
 This is a surprise. How are you?

1258
01:10:52,160 --> 01:10:54,079
 - l'm good.
 - Oh, you look great.

1259
01:10:54,080 --> 01:10:57,080
 - So do you.
 - Oh, thank you.

1260
01:10:57,760 --> 01:11:00,760
 Hello, Mary.
 l'm Tom. l'm his father. l live here.

1261
01:11:00,840 --> 01:11:03,159
 Oh, Tom.

1262
01:11:03,160 --> 01:11:04,919
 My two favourite men.

1263
01:11:04,920 --> 01:11:06,399
 ln you go.

1264
01:11:06,400 --> 01:11:08,319
 - You never rang me.
 - l'm sorry.

1265
01:11:08,320 --> 01:11:11,320
 Whatever happened to that drink
 we were gonna have?

1266
01:11:11,440 --> 01:11:14,319
 - l've got a surprise for you.
 - Oh, Joe, you shouldn't have.

1267
01:11:14,320 --> 01:11:16,599
 - Hello.
 - Katie, this is Mary. Mary, this is Katie.

1268
01:11:16,600 --> 01:11:18,599
 - Hello, Mary. lt's nice to meet you.
 - Oh, hi.

1269
01:11:18,600 --> 01:11:20,999
 GERRl: This is Joe's girlfriend.
 - l like your jacket.

1270
01:11:21,000 --> 01:11:22,879
 Your mum gave me a pot of basil. Smell that.

1271
01:11:22,880 --> 01:11:24,959
 - She's going to make him some pesto.
 - Lovely.

1272
01:11:24,960 --> 01:11:27,319
 - Shall l take your jacket, Mary?
 - Yeah, thanks, Tom.

1273
01:11:27,320 --> 01:11:29,959
 - How are you, Mary?
 - Yeah, l'm really good, thanks, yeah.

1274
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:32,960
 - How was your journey?
 - lt was all right.

1275
01:11:33,880 --> 01:11:36,839
 - Oh, no, it wasn't actually.
 - Didn't get lost again, did you?

1276
01:11:36,840 --> 01:11:39,840
 Oh, no, the journey was all right.
 lt's the car.

1277
01:11:39,960 --> 01:11:41,679
 TOM: ls it OK?
 GERRl: What happened?

1278
01:11:41,680 --> 01:11:43,519
 - lt wouldn't start.
 - Oh, no.

1279
01:11:43,520 --> 01:11:46,159
 Yeah, it's a nightmare.
 l had to come on the tube.

1280
01:11:46,160 --> 01:11:48,119
 And it got broken into last night.

1281
01:11:48,120 --> 01:11:50,079
 - Oh, sorry to hear that.
 - Oh, no.

1282
01:11:50,080 --> 01:11:52,999
 Yeah, l did my big weekly
 supermarket shop yesterday,

1283
01:11:53,000 --> 01:11:55,919
 which is great, l couldn't do that
 before l had the car.

1284
01:11:55,920 --> 01:11:58,920
 l went nice and early,
 so it wouldn't be dark when l got back.

1285
01:11:59,080 --> 01:12:02,080
 l brought three bags in, but l must have
 left the fourth one on the front seat.

1286
01:12:03,120 --> 01:12:05,639
 l got in. l thought, that's great, that's done,

1287
01:12:05,640 --> 01:12:08,559
 l can chill out now
 and have a nice little glass ofwine.

1288
01:12:08,560 --> 01:12:10,599
 l had a really nice evening, actually.

1289
01:12:10,600 --> 01:12:11,599
 Er...

1290
01:12:11,600 --> 01:12:14,600
 But then, this morning,
 l'm in the bathroom, l'm sitting on...

1291
01:12:14,840 --> 01:12:17,399
 Cos it's the toilet roll that l've left in the car.

1292
01:12:17,400 --> 01:12:19,839
 So, l rush out
 and my window's been smashed.

1293
01:12:19,840 --> 01:12:21,799
 There's glass everywhere

1294
01:12:21,800 --> 01:12:23,999
 and all my toilet rolls have been stolen.

1295
01:12:24,000 --> 01:12:26,319
 - lt's probably kids.
 MARY: l think you're right.

1296
01:12:26,320 --> 01:12:28,479
 Are you insured, Mary?

1297
01:12:28,480 --> 01:12:31,479
 - Yeah, of course l'm insured.
 - Well, that's something, isn't it?

1298
01:12:31,480 --> 01:12:33,799
 You can't drive a car without insurance.
 lt's illegal.

1299
01:12:33,800 --> 01:12:36,359
 l know. At least you'll be able
 to claim for your window.

1300
01:12:36,360 --> 01:12:37,639
 l know.

1301
01:12:37,640 --> 01:12:40,640
 Anyway, l'm... l'm sick of it. l just left it.
 lt's just a car. What does it matter?

1302
01:12:41,800 --> 01:12:43,639
 GERRl:
 Go on. Sit yourself down, Mary.

1303
01:12:43,640 --> 01:12:46,640
 - Put the kettle on, Tom.
 - Yeah, yeah. Good idea.

1304
01:12:47,520 --> 01:12:49,479
 lt's given me a lot of stress, Tom.

1305
01:12:49,480 --> 01:12:52,319
 This car's been a catalogue of disaster, hasn't
 it?

1306
01:12:52,320 --> 01:12:53,519
 l know.

1307
01:12:53,520 --> 01:12:55,279
 Cut your losses, Mary. Get rid of it.

1308
01:12:55,280 --> 01:12:58,079
 But l've spent so much on it, Tom.
 l can't just sell it now.

1309
01:12:58,080 --> 01:13:00,599
 But if you keep it,
 it's only going to get worse.

1310
01:13:00,600 --> 01:13:03,079
 - Well, you know what l think, Mary.
 - Yeah, yeah.

1311
01:13:03,080 --> 01:13:05,359
 l'm fed up with it, to be honest, Tom.

1312
01:13:05,360 --> 01:13:07,279
 l've had three punctures.

1313
01:13:07,280 --> 01:13:08,959
 - Three punctures?
 - Yeah.

1314
01:13:08,960 --> 01:13:11,919
 My exhaust has fallen off. l had to get
 a new one. My carburettor went.

1315
01:13:11,920 --> 01:13:14,039
 You can't take it back
 to the guys you got it from?

1316
01:13:14,040 --> 01:13:17,040
 No. They'd guarantee the labour for three
 months, but not the parts. Bastards.

1317
01:13:17,840 --> 01:13:20,639
 Other way round, isn't it?
 Parts for three months, not labour.

1318
01:13:20,640 --> 01:13:22,759
 No.

1319
01:13:22,760 --> 01:13:24,399
 Oh, yeah, that's right.

1320
01:13:24,400 --> 01:13:27,400
 Oh, l don't know. Anyway...
 my windscreen wiper got ripped off.

1321
01:13:27,600 --> 01:13:29,839
 l got three points for speeding, at 60 each.

1322
01:13:29,840 --> 01:13:32,239
 So, l've got nine points on my driving licence.

1323
01:13:32,240 --> 01:13:33,599
 - Haven't l, Gerri?
 - Yes.

1324
01:13:33,600 --> 01:13:35,159
 lt keeps making funny noises.

1325
01:13:35,160 --> 01:13:38,160
 l got towed away and l wasn't even
 parked on a double-yellow line.

1326
01:13:38,400 --> 01:13:41,400
 l've got seven parking tickets...
 no, nine parking tickets.

1327
01:13:41,840 --> 01:13:43,239
 And then...

1328
01:13:43,240 --> 01:13:46,039
 l broke down on the motorway
 on the way to Brighton

1329
01:13:46,040 --> 01:13:47,999
 and l got towed to Crawley,

1330
01:13:48,000 --> 01:13:51,000
 which is the last place l want to go,
 because l grew up there and l hate it.

1331
01:13:51,440 --> 01:13:54,440
 So, l had to get the train home and then
 the train back to Crawley the next day

1332
01:13:55,120 --> 01:13:56,919
 and the guy kept trying to touch me up.

1333
01:13:56,920 --> 01:13:59,920
 lt cost me nearly 500 and l never even
 got my weekend in Brighton.

1334
01:14:00,080 --> 01:14:02,199
 That was supposed to be my summer holiday.

1335
01:14:02,200 --> 01:14:03,079
 Yes.

1336
01:14:03,080 --> 01:14:04,879
 - lt's not fair, is it?
 - No.

1337
01:14:04,880 --> 01:14:07,559
 - Well, never mind.
 - Come and sit down, Mary. Relax.

1338
01:14:07,560 --> 01:14:10,560
 - Yeah, thanks, Joe.
 - At least you're here now, eh?

1339
01:14:10,960 --> 01:14:13,919
 - What did you say your name was?
 - Katie.

1340
01:14:13,920 --> 01:14:16,239
 MARY:
 Oh.

1341
01:14:16,240 --> 01:14:19,240
 Well, the good news is, Mary,
 l've made a cake in your honour.

1342
01:14:19,400 --> 01:14:20,759
 Oh, thanks, Gerri.

1343
01:14:20,760 --> 01:14:23,119
 TOM: She knew you were coming,
 so she baked a cake!

1344
01:14:23,120 --> 01:14:26,039
 - Don't forget to give me the recipe.
 - No, l won't forget, Katie.

1345
01:14:26,040 --> 01:14:28,319
 - You haven't tasted it yet.
 - Oh, it smells nice.

1346
01:14:28,320 --> 01:14:31,320
 Yeah, l wouldn't mind having the recipe
 for that. l've never baked a cake before.

1347
01:14:32,080 --> 01:14:34,319
 - Of course you can.
 - You can have a cake-off!

1348
01:14:34,320 --> 01:14:37,039
 Oh, l don't think so.
 l tried making a fruit cake once.

1349
01:14:37,040 --> 01:14:39,559
 Everything sank to the bottom.
 lt was horrible.

1350
01:14:39,560 --> 01:14:41,199
 You're a good cook.

1351
01:14:41,200 --> 01:14:44,200
 Thank you.

1352
01:14:44,680 --> 01:14:47,680
 - What about these two, then, Mary?
 - Such a surprise.

1353
01:14:47,720 --> 01:14:50,720
 This monster hid this young lady
 behind the sitting-room door.

1354
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:54,320
 - Made me jump.
 - l nearly gave poor Tom a heart attack.

1355
01:14:54,440 --> 01:14:55,799
 She passed the test.

1356
01:14:55,800 --> 01:14:58,800
 Surprised you passed the test.
 l'd have got rid of you on the spot.

1357
01:14:59,200 --> 01:15:00,879
 A terrible way to treat someone.

1358
01:15:00,880 --> 01:15:03,880
 KATlE: Yeah.
 - We had absolutely no idea.

1359
01:15:04,200 --> 01:15:05,959
 - My big secret.
 - Oh, thanks very much.

1360
01:15:05,960 --> 01:15:07,919
 lt's obviously serious.

1361
01:15:07,920 --> 01:15:10,920
 Still, it's been really good to meet you both,
 though, and we had a lovely lunch.

1362
01:15:12,080 --> 01:15:13,719
 You didn't say you were having lunch.

1363
01:15:13,720 --> 01:15:16,720
 - We have lunch every day.
 - l know you have lunch every day, Joe.

1364
01:15:17,280 --> 01:15:18,639
 Bread and cheese.

1365
01:15:18,640 --> 01:15:21,279
 - Nothing special.
 - l thought it was special.

1366
01:15:21,280 --> 01:15:24,280
 We had some tomatoes from Tom
 and Gerri's allotment. Have you tasted them?

1367
01:15:24,760 --> 01:15:27,760
 Loads oftimes. Gerri's always giving me
 stuff, aren't you, Gerri?

1368
01:15:28,120 --> 01:15:30,719
 - l'll give you some to take home, Mary.
 - Oh, great.

1369
01:15:30,720 --> 01:15:33,720
 Oh, yeah, l can take them on the tube.

1370
01:15:33,960 --> 01:15:35,919
 So, what is it you do, then, Jackie?

1371
01:15:35,920 --> 01:15:38,519
 KATlE:
 Katie.

1372
01:15:38,520 --> 01:15:41,520
 - Katie.
 - Don't worry. An occupational therapist.

1373
01:15:42,720 --> 01:15:43,719
 Oh.

1374
01:15:43,720 --> 01:15:46,720
 GERRl: She looks after stroke victims
 and the elderly.

1375
01:15:46,760 --> 01:15:49,760
 And...l grew up just down the road
 from you, in Croydon.

1376
01:15:51,440 --> 01:15:54,440
