 - Yeah.

1774
01:42:22,160 --> 01:42:25,160
 Do you want a cuddle?

1775
01:42:33,160 --> 01:42:35,399
 You sure you don't want some tea?

1776
01:42:35,400 --> 01:42:38,400
 - Aye, go on, then.
 - Yeah.

1777
01:42:45,840 --> 01:42:48,840
 Ooh, that's better.

1778
01:42:50,640 --> 01:42:53,640
 lt's really lovely to be here.

1779
01:42:53,760 --> 01:42:56,760
 l haven't been for months.

1780
01:42:58,120 --> 01:43:01,120
 They invite me a lot.
 We're really old friends.

1781
01:43:07,720 --> 01:43:09,759
 Are you sleeping in Joe's room?

1782
01:43:09,760 --> 01:43:11,039
 Yeah.

1783
01:43:11,040 --> 01:43:12,879
 Oh, yeah.

1784
01:43:12,880 --> 01:43:15,880
 All his little bits and bobs.

1785
01:43:19,400 --> 01:43:20,879
 Did he go to the funeral?

1786
01:43:20,880 --> 01:43:23,599
 Yeah.

1787
01:43:23,600 --> 01:43:25,559
 With his girlfriend?

1788
01:43:25,560 --> 01:43:28,560
 - No.
 - Oh.

1789
01:43:29,920 --> 01:43:32,599
 They're coming round later.

1790
01:43:32,600 --> 01:43:35,600
 Oh, are they?

1791
01:43:42,400 --> 01:43:45,400
 Sorry l'm such a mess.

1792
01:43:46,080 --> 01:43:49,080
 l didn't get to bed till five
 and then l couldn't sleep.

1793
01:43:52,320 --> 01:43:55,320
 l just got up and came straight here.

1794
01:44:03,160 --> 01:44:06,160
 Does Gerri ever mention me?

1795
01:44:07,160 --> 01:44:08,879
 No.

1796
01:44:08,880 --> 01:44:11,199
 Mary.

1797
01:44:11,200 --> 01:44:14,200
 No.

1798
01:44:29,320 --> 01:44:32,320
 You look like Tom.

1799
01:44:32,360 --> 01:44:34,039
 Oh, aye?

1800
01:44:34,040 --> 01:44:37,040
 Yeah.

1801
01:44:37,440 --> 01:44:40,440
 You've got a nice face.

1802
01:44:41,360 --> 01:44:44,360
 Tom's got a nice face, too.

1803
01:44:47,720 --> 01:44:50,359
 What was your wife's name?

1804
01:44:50,360 --> 01:44:53,360
 - Linda.
 - Oh.

1805
01:44:53,720 --> 01:44:56,720
 Was she nice?

1806
01:45:13,920 --> 01:45:15,519
 Did you have dinner last night?

1807
01:45:15,520 --> 01:45:18,520
 - We had chicken.
 - Oh, lovely.

1808
01:45:19,800 --> 01:45:22,800
 - They're good cooks, aren't they?
 - Yeah.

1809
01:45:23,800 --> 01:45:26,159
 l can't cook.

1810
01:45:26,160 --> 01:45:29,160
 - Can you cook?
 - Nah.

1811
01:45:33,960 --> 01:45:36,960
 l didn't really eat anything yesterday.

1812
01:45:37,440 --> 01:45:40,440
 Do you want some toast?

1813
01:45:43,960 --> 01:45:46,960
 No, l'm all right, thank you.

1814
01:45:50,600 --> 01:45:53,359
 Wouldn't mind a cigarette, though.

1815
01:45:53,360 --> 01:45:55,719
 - Do you smoke?
 - Yeah.

1816
01:45:55,720 --> 01:45:58,720
 Oh, good.

1817
01:45:59,480 --> 01:46:02,480
 Oh, yeah. My friend used to roll her own.

1818
01:46:05,200 --> 01:46:07,559
 Do you want one ofthese?

1819
01:46:07,560 --> 01:46:10,560
 No, it's all right.
 l'll have one of mine.

1820
01:46:11,000 --> 01:46:13,719
 Oh, no, go on, then.
 For old time's sake.

1821
01:46:13,720 --> 01:46:16,720
 Yeah.

1822
01:46:17,560 --> 01:46:20,560
 We have to go out there.

1823
01:46:21,720 --> 01:46:24,720
 Oh, we can stay in here, can't we?
 They won't know.

1824
01:46:37,720 --> 01:46:40,279
 Ooh.

1825
01:46:40,280 --> 01:46:43,280
 Takes me back.

1826
01:46:44,560 --> 01:46:47,560
 Did you ever smoke dope?

1827
01:46:47,760 --> 01:46:50,399
 Tried it a few times.

1828
01:46:50,400 --> 01:46:52,919
 We used to.

1829
01:46:52,920 --> 01:46:55,920
 Me and my best friend, Monica.

1830
01:46:56,600 --> 01:46:59,600
 Don't see her any more.

1831
01:47:00,680 --> 01:47:03,559
 Did you like the Beatles?

1832
01:47:03,560 --> 01:47:05,559
 They were all right.

1833
01:47:05,560 --> 01:47:08,039
 l was more Elvis. Jerry Lee Lewis.

1834
01:47:08,040 --> 01:47:10,919
 Yeah.

1835
01:47:10,920 --> 01:47:12,479
  l'm all shook up

1836
01:47:12,480 --> 01:47:15,480
 Heh.

1837
01:47:20,840 --> 01:47:22,279
 Have you got any children?

1838
01:47:22,280 --> 01:47:25,280
 Got a son.

1839
01:47:25,720 --> 01:47:28,720
 ls he married?

1840
01:47:29,280 --> 01:47:32,280
 Don't know.

1841
01:47:39,840 --> 01:47:41,879
 You got kids?

1842
01:47:41,880 --> 01:47:44,880
 No.

1843
01:47:45,920 --> 01:47:48,920
 Unfortunately.

1844
01:47:57,200 --> 01:47:59,919
 Have you got to go back soon?

1845
01:47:59,920 --> 01:48:02,920
 Yeah. Got a few things to sort out.

1846
01:48:03,680 --> 01:48:05,879
 l don't suppose your son will help you.

1847
01:48:05,880 --> 01:48:08,880
 Nah.

1848
01:48:20,080 --> 01:48:23,080
 l could come up and give you a hand,
 if you like.

1849
01:48:24,280 --> 01:48:26,199
 Have you got to move?

1850
01:48:26,200 --> 01:48:29,200
 No.

1851
01:48:29,960 --> 01:48:32,960
 l could take a few days offwork.

1852
01:48:36,120 --> 01:48:39,120
 Are you warm enough?

1853
01:48:39,760 --> 01:48:41,879
 Oh, l'll be all right.

1854
01:48:41,880 --> 01:48:44,880
 We'll just finish these.

1855
01:48:53,680 --> 01:48:55,919
 Oh, do you know Ken?

1856
01:48:55,920 --> 01:48:57,639
 Ken?

1857
01:48:57,640 --> 01:48:59,159
 Yeah.

1858
01:48:59,160 --> 01:49:02,160
 Yeah. Did he go to the funeral?

1859
01:49:02,240 --> 01:49:04,559
 No.

1860
01:49:04,560 --> 01:49:07,560
 He's a bit weird, isn't he?

1861
01:49:07,600 --> 01:49:10,600
 ls he?

1862
01:49:20,280 --> 01:49:23,280
 l don't really smoke.

1863
01:49:26,120 --> 01:49:29,120
 l had too much to drink last night.

1864
01:49:29,480 --> 01:49:31,799
 l had a bit of a bad day.

1865
01:49:31,800 --> 01:49:34,800
 My car broke down.
 lt had to be towed away.

1866
01:49:36,120 --> 01:49:39,120
 They said it wasn't worth repairing.
 They gave me 20 quid for it.

1867
01:49:39,440 --> 01:49:42,440
 - That's not much.
 - No. What can you do with 20 quid?

1868
01:49:45,480 --> 01:49:48,039
 l bought myself a bottle of champagne.

1869
01:49:48,040 --> 01:49:50,719
 Yeah?

1870
01:49:50,720 --> 01:49:53,720
 Yeah.

1871
01:49:56,760 --> 01:49:59,760
 Did you finish it?

1872
01:50:01,040 --> 01:50:02,359
 Yeah, l did.

1873
01:50:02,360 --> 01:50:04,999
 Huh.

1874
01:50:05,000 --> 01:50:08,000
 (Mary sniffles)

